&lt;p&gt;Understanding &lt;code&gt;async&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;await&lt;/code&gt;, and Concurrency in Python — A Simple Tutorial&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re learning Python and find terms like &lt;code&gt;async&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;await&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;concurrent tasks&lt;/code&gt; confusing — you’re not alone! This tutorial explains how to write Python code that runs &lt;strong&gt;multiple tasks simultaneously&lt;/strong&gt;, such as reading data from the internet, analyzing logs, and fetching records from a remote server.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
